entries.d:
a. A combining form or prefix from Gr. poly`s, many; as,
polygon, a figure of many angles; polyatomic, having many atoms;
polychord, polyconic.

n. A clinic in which diseases of many sorts are treated;
especially, an institution in which clinical instruction is given in
all kinds of disease.

a. Bearing fruit repeatedly, as most perennial plants;
polycarpic.
a. Producing many or young.

plural of pondering
v reflect deeply on a subject
s deeply or seriously thoughtful;

a. Mingled or interspersed with poppies.
a. Affected with poppy juice; hence, figuratively, drugged;
drowsy; listless; inactive.
